I'm enjoying my Gamecube immensely. PSO Ep1&amp;2 is just a blast. Far better community (for some reason) than the DC one. Aside from a few clueless forces, just about any pickup game is a blast. With friends, well, funfunfun (and I'm serious about the fun, unlike what I posted on the AO boards). Metroid Prime for the GC is just mindblowing. That game alone is enough reason to buy a GC. Simply amazing. You don't see these special effects on the Xbox (not yet anyway...Halo 2...Halo 2...).<br>
<br>
I, too, have an Xbox and Halo is one of the all time great games. Unfortunately, it's one of the only games worth playing on the 'box, but there looks to be some good stuff in the pipleline heading our way. Still, my 'box does yeoman service as a DVD player, so no real complaints about MS's pathetic release lineup for it. <br>
<br>
