<br>
Here's what I will do when I build my dream machine (next year):<br>
<br>
Black Aluminum case with black Floppy and 500w power<br>
AMD Athlon XP (Probably 2600 or 2700)<br>
nForce2 motherboard (with 8x AGP)<br>
512mb-1gb PC2700 DDR memory <br>
Geforce FX vid card (unless the price is too outrageous, then  <br>
    at the very least a 128 mb Radeon 9700 Pro)<br>
80 or 120 GB 7200 rpm HD<br>
16x DVD ROM (black)<br>
48x 24x 48x CD-RW (unless they have something faster by <br>
    that time) black<br>
SoundBlaster Audigy 2 Platinum sound card.<br>
<br>
That, of course, are just the core components. I already have a good monitor (LCDs are NOT the best monitors for games) and a good set of speakers (although I might upgrade simply because of the new sound card), so if I went for the low end version of the above machine, it would cost me about $1600 in components. The high end, probably around $2.2k or a little more. Those are machines that will last for 3-4 years (with maybe a vid card and memory upgrade or two), and play all of the games coming out within the next two years with no problems. My P3 866 machine cost me over $3k brand new 2 years ago (It's a Dell) and I have upgraded memory and video cards since then. So it pays to shop around and know how to build your own box.<br>
<br>
