<br>
If you go nVidia nForce mobo, you don't need an add-in soundcard. The nForce has full Dolby 5.1 built in. From all reports, it's very nice. Just add Klipsch 5.1s and wait for the cops to show up...<br>
<br>
Hard drives. Go BIG. Also, get serial ATA. By DOOMsday, this'll be almost mandatory and it'll be standard on mobos. May as well use it and keep HD thrashing to a minimum. <br>
<br>
As for quitting AO, well, by this time next year I'm sure I'll be history. As for now, well, I was just tooling about northern Rubi-ka with my pistol ADV, and those towers...those are kinda neat really. You see them...and just want to fiddle with them yourself. Then you realize...well...I dunno. I want to like this stuff, but sooooooooo many annoyances getting into it. I still think PvP is a gross mistake in these games. It just doesn't balance well with PvM at all.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aomunkie>AOMunkie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Peking Duck</span><br>  Posts: 191<br> <font color=#660000>(12/2/02 11:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2154.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://munkiesuthorn.freewebspace.com/aosig.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: indeed the new changes make me wonder</span><hr size=1> “We are all quiting AO…”<br>
