<br>
The problem is the average player is getting forced out of the game. <br>
<br>
I don't have any problems with my MAs (no more than usual anyway). My problem is I don't want to PvP, I don't want to be part of some so-called guild, and I don't want FC dictating my behavior ingame. <br>
<br>
PvP is a waste of time, period. If I want to shoot up other people online there are many far better ways to do it other than AO. AO, like most MMRPGs, is stat-driven. Stat driven PvP is all about equipment and subject to the worst aspects of creeping featurism. I didn't like it in EQ (though I was fairly good at it), I really didn't like it in DAoC (because it was so unbalanced), and I don't want to do it in AO because of all the past exploits, present and past nerfs, and I'd need to be part of some rapacious pack of uber-guild powergaming vermin to keep up with the feature creep. No thanks. <br>
<br>
Still, FC insists on forcing all of us in that direction. And I, for one, don't want to go there. So far, I still don't have to, but my ADV wanderings show me the writing on the wall. <br>
<br>
Wandering around towers and overlapping 25% zones...it's an org world now, and that's exactly what I came to AO to avoid. The chance to adventure in small parties, solo, or whatever. Now it's becoming Velious, where you need 20 to 40 people to do anything. Without guild support...forget it. I've had enough of power guilds in EQ. Been there, done that, have the t-shirt and the action figure. <br>
<br>
I don't want to do it again. I don't have time or the inclination to make time. That's why I've about had enough of AO, MA or no.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showMessageRange?topicID=2154.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=2154.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showNextMessage?topicID=2154.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2154.topic&index=34><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/far_east/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.emailToFriend?topicID=2154.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.threadControl?topicID=2154.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/far_east/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2154.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2154.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notifi